<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Palpus black and reduced to stubs. Male fore tarsomeres 3–5 with elongate hair-like setae dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[357,365,382,396]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
and CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[476,484,382,396]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
bare. Pregonite elongate and narrow, with pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[1142,1228,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Phallus elongate and gently curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[473,558,406,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Acrophallus elongate and without spines (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1132,406,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" box="[199,751,442,467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,442,467]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,417,442,467]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Male.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[575,661,442,467]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" unit="mm" value="4.6">4.6 mm</quantity>
(n = 1).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
Head. Frons distinctly protruding giving the head a trapezoidal profile. Fronto-orbital and parafacial plates covered with silver microtrichia. Fronto-orbital plate with some small scattered setulae in addition to 9 frontal setae continuing on to parafacial plate to below level of aristal insertion in lateral view. Frontal vitta black, narrowing towards lunule. Inner vertical setae differentiated, outer vertical setae developed [but both broken]. Ocellar setae of about the same length as frontal setae; 2 reclinate and 2 proclinate fronto-orbital setae arranged in partly overlapping rows with anterior reclinate orbital seta positioned anterior to posterior proclinate seta (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T. &amp; Dahlem, G. A." pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="1313 - 1335" refId="ref8565" refString="Pape, T. &amp; Dahlem, G. A. (2010) Sarcophagidae. In: Brown, B. V., Borkent, A., Cumming, J. M., Wood, D. M., Woodley, N. E. &amp; Zumbado, M. (Eds.), Manual of Central American Diptera. Uol. 2. NRC Research Press, Ottawa, pp. 1313 - 1335." type="book chapter" year="2010">Pape &amp; Dahlem 2010</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 6). Antenna dark brown, first flagellomere with gray microtrichia; arista thickened in proximal half and as long as first flagellomere. Palpus black, reduced to a rudimentary stub.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
Thorax. Black, with silvery microtrichia. Chaetotaxy: acrostichals 0+1, dorsocentrals 2+3, intra-alars 1+2, supra-alars 2+3, postpronotals 2, postalars 2, notopleurals 2, anepisternals 4–5, katepisternals 3, merals 10, scutellum with 1 pair of basal setae, 1 pair of lateral setae, 1 pair of apical setae and no discal setae. 
<emphasis box="[1316,1369,840,863]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Legs</emphasis>
. Fore femur with row of setae on posterodorsal and posteroventral surfaces. Fore tarsomere 3 with two long, hair-like setae dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[319,403,910,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Fore tarsomere 4 with one long, hair-like seta dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1040,1125,910,935]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Fore tarsomere 5 with one long dorsally seta (
<figureCitation box="[367,452,946,971]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Mid tibia without anterodorsal and anteroventral setae. Hind femur with row of setae on posterodorsal and posteroventral surfaces. 
<emphasis box="[684,740,984,1007]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline. Tegula dark brown. Basicosta yellowish. Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1428,1436,998,1012]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
bare. Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[295,319,1036,1050]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">4+5</subScript>
with setae dorsally. Vein CuA 
<subScript attach="left" box="[669,677,1036,1050]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">1</subScript>
bare. Costal spine not differentiated. Third costal section without ventral setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
Abdomen. Black with silvery-gray microtrichia in about anterior half of each tergite. Microtrichia on tergites 3 and 4 interrupted by a median black stripe. Syntergite 1+2 without marginal setae. Tergites 3 and 4 with a pair of median marginal setae. Tergite 5 with a row of marginal setae. 
<emphasis box="[893,1020,1168,1193]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Terminalia.</emphasis>
Tergite 6, syntergosternite 7+8 and epandrium brown. Cercus dark brown, shorter than epandrium in lateral view, with distal portion abruptly narrowing towards apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[609,695,1240,1265]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Basal portion of cercus covered with many long setae (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,1240,1265]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Ventral margin of cercal prong slightly curved; cercal apex rounded (
<figureCitation box="[917,1000,1276,1301]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Cercal prongs, in dorsal view, narrow and parallel (
<figureCitation box="[297,381,1312,1337]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). Surstylus dark brown, about half the length of cercus, with distal half narrowing toward apex and curved dorsally; with microtrichia restricted to basal half (
<figureCitation box="[851,935,1348,1373]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Pregonite elongate, longer than postgonite, narrowed and curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[521,607,1384,1409]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Postgonite longer than wide, with a long pre-apical seta and a row of small setae along ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[530,614,1420,1445]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
). Phallus elongate, gently curved ventrally, with ventral and dorsal plates well developed (
<figureCitation box="[342,430,1456,1481]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Distiphallus with a distinct ventral swelling, with many membranous cuticular spines (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1492,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Acrophallus elongate and rounded apically, with some wrinkles and without cuticular spines (
<figureCitation box="[1312,1397,1492,1517]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" box="[199,415,1528,1553]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis box="[199,291,1528,1553]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1564,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho-Filho &amp; Gorayeb &amp; Soares &amp; Souza, 2018" authorityName="Carvalho-Filho &amp; Gorayeb &amp; Soares &amp; Souza" authorityYear="2018" box="[323,468,1565,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fofo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,468,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Metopia fofo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[476,566,1564,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[476,566,1564,1589]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
runs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sabrosky" authorityName="Sabrosky" box="[660,986,1564,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krombeini">
<emphasis box="[660,874,1564,1589]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Metopia krombeini</emphasis>
Sabrosky
</taxonomicName>
in the most recent key to the American species of 
<emphasis box="[273,366,1601,1624]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Metopia</emphasis>
Meigen (
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T." box="[478,615,1601,1625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="81 - 101" refId="ref8396" refString="Pape, T. (1987 a) Revision of Neotropical Metopia Meigen (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Systematic Entomology, 12, 81 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1987. tb 00550. x" type="journal article" year="1987">Pape 1987a</bibRefCitation>
), but differs from this species in having phallus gently curved ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[159,242,1636,1661]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), acrophallus without spines and rounded apically (
<figureCitation box="[813,896,1636,1661]" captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), and cercal prong narrowed in dorsal view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 22–26" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1915,1938]" captionTargetBox="[206,1397,208,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[191,1401,193,1898]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 22–26. Metopia fofo sp. nov., holotype ♂. 22. Right fore tarsus, dorsal view. 23. Epandrium, surstylus and cercus, left lateral view. 24. Cerci, dorsal view. 25. Gonites, left lateral view. 26. Phallus, left lateral view. Abbreviations: acp = acrophallus; dpl = dorsal plate; prg = pregonite; ptg = postgonite; vpl = ventral plate. Scale bars: 0.1 mm (Figs 22–25); 0.2 mm (Fig. 21)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2606519/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName box="[233,382,1672,1697]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="krombeini">
<emphasis box="[233,382,1672,1697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">M. krombeini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the phallus is almost straight, the acrophallus has small cuticular spines and is subrectangular apically, and the cercal prong has an enlarged base and narrow tip (
<bibRefCitation author="Pape, T." box="[904,1216,1708,1733]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" pagination="81 - 101" refId="ref8396" refString="Pape, T. (1987 a) Revision of Neotropical Metopia Meigen (Diptera: Sarcophagidae). Systematic Entomology, 12, 81 - 101. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 3113.1987. tb 00550. x" type="journal article" year="1987">Pape 1987a: figs 27, 30, 33</bibRefCitation>
). The phallus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho-Filho &amp; Gorayeb &amp; Soares &amp; Souza, 2018" authorityName="Carvalho-Filho &amp; Gorayeb &amp; Soares &amp; Souza" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fofo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">M. fofo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[203,295,1744,1769]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[203,295,1744,1769]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Allen" authorityName="Allen" box="[590,806,1744,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateropili">
<emphasis box="[590,732,1744,1769]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">M. lateropili</emphasis>
Allen
</taxonomicName>
, since both share a distinct ventral swelling with many membranous cuticular spines. 
<taxonomicName box="[506,714,1780,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lateropili">
<emphasis box="[506,714,1780,1805]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Metopia lateropili</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Carvalho-Filho &amp; Gorayeb &amp; Soares &amp; Souza, 2018" authorityName="Carvalho-Filho &amp; Gorayeb &amp; Soares &amp; Souza" authorityYear="2018" box="[876,962,1781,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Sarcophagidae" genus="Metopia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fofo" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[876,962,1781,1805]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">M. fofo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[974,1068,1780,1805]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[974,1068,1780,1805]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having palpus elongate, not reduced to a stub.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,733,1852,1877]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" box="[199,733,1852,1877]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1852,1877]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Distribution.</emphasis>
NEOTROPICAL—Brazil (
<collectingRegion box="[665,721,1853,1877]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Pará</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="409" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,1949]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1888,1913]" pageId="8" pageNumber="409">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the word “fofó”, which is a famous popular festival that takes place before the carnival in the streets of Cametá (the type-locality).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
